      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver must be under version control with documented test suite and release validation reports.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 is used under a controlled software environment with documented version history, regression test suite, and FDA-recognized solver validation documentation. Achieved level meets required level for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations via benchmark test cases.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver has been verified against standard benchmark cases including lid-driven cavity and backward-facing step flows. Results agree with published reference solutions within accepted tolerances, confirming correct numerical implementation of the incompressible Navier-Stokes equations."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be documented and discretization error must be below 5% for primary QoI.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry. GCI for the scalar stress-based hemolysis index was computed at 2.1%, confirming adequate spatial resolution. The fine mesh (6.8 million polyhedral cells) was selected for production runs. Achieved level exceeds required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must be documented with sufficient detail to reproduce boundary conditions in the CFD model.",
      "rationale": "The FDA interlaboratory hemolysis study provides fully documented test conditions including fluid temperature (37°C), hematocrit (30%), inlet flow rates (2.5 and 5.0 L/min), and rotational speeds (2500 and 3500 RPM). These conditions are faithfully reproduced as CFD boundary conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted hemolysis index must agree with experimental measurements within combined experimental and numerical uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) predictions at all five validated operating points fall within the experimental interquartile range reported across FDA interlaboratory participants. Maximum normalized error is 18%, within the acceptance criterion accounting for biological variability in the power-law hemolysis model constants."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI used in validation must be the same metric used in the regulatory decision criterion.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index (RH) used as the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate device) is directly computed from the same NIH predictions validated against experimental data. No intermediate transformation introduces additional unvalidated model components."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, fluid properties, and operating conditions must be sufficiently similar to the COU device and conditions.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump, which shares the same impeller topology and operating envelope as the subject CPB device. Fluid properties (blood analog and porcine blood) bracket the clinical operating range. Validation conditions span the COU operating space."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 when solver is commercially validated and discretization error is separately characterized.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, iterative and round-off errors are not required to be separately quantified provided that convergence criteria are documented. Residuals were driven below 1e-5 for all equations; solver error is subsumed within the discretization error assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
